# Section 4: Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 TCP Client-Server Communication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant ClientApp as Client Process
    participant ClientSock as Client Socket
    participant ServerSock as Server Socket
    participant ServerApp as Server Process

    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: INITIALIZATION PHASE
    ClientApp->>ClientSock: socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, 0)
    ServerApp->>ServerSock: socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, 0)
    ServerApp->>ServerSock: bind(INADDR_ANY, port=8080)
    ServerApp->>ServerSock: listen(backlog=5)

    Note over ClientSock,ServerSock: TCP 3-WAY HANDSHAKE
    ClientSock->>ServerSock: SYN (seq=x)
    ServerSock-->>ClientSock: SYN-ACK (seq=y, ack=x+1)
    ClientSock->>ServerSock: ACK (seq=x+1, ack=y+1)

    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: CONNECTION ACCEPTED
    ServerSock->>ServerApp: accept() returns new_socket
    Note over ServerSock,ServerApp: Server forked/threaded connection

    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: DATA EXCHANGE - MATRIX TRANSFER
    ClientApp->>ClientSock: send(matrix_size_n)
    ClientSock->>ServerSock: TCP Segment (4 bytes)
    ServerSock->>ServerApp: recv() -> n
    ClientApp->>ClientSock: send(matrix_elements)
    ClientSock->>ServerSock: TCP Segments (n*n * 4 bytes)
    ServerSock->>ServerApp: recv() -> A[n][n]

    Note over ServerApp: CLASSIFICATION LOGIC
    ServerApp->>ServerApp: Check Diagonal (priority 1)
    alt isDiagonal == true
        ServerApp->>ServerApp: result = DIAGONAL
    else isDiagonal == false
        ServerApp->>ServerApp: Check Upper Triangular (priority 2)
        alt isUpper == true
            ServerApp->>ServerApp: result = UPPER TRIANGULAR
        else isUpper == false
            ServerApp->>ServerApp: Check Lower Triangular (priority 3)
            alt isLower == true
                ServerApp->>ServerApp: result = LOWER TRIANGULAR
            else isLower == false
                ServerApp->>ServerApp: result = NONE
            end
        end
    end

    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: RESPONSE TRANSFER
    ServerApp->>ServerSock: send(result_string)
    ServerSock->>ClientSock: TCP Segment
    ClientSock->>ClientApp: recv() -> result
    ClientApp->>ClientApp: Print result to console

    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: CONNECTION TERMINATION (4-Way)
    ClientSock->>ServerSock: FIN
    ServerSock-->>ClientSock: ACK
    ServerSock->>ClientSock: FIN
    ClientSock-->>ServerSock: ACK
    Note over ClientApp,ServerApp: Both sockets CLOSED
```

---

## 4.2 Matrix Classification Logic Flow (Server-Side)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Server receives matrix A nxn]) --> CheckDim{n x n SQUARE?}
    CheckDim -- No --> NotSquare[Return NOT A SPECIAL MATRIX]
    CheckDim -- Yes --> InitFlags[Initialize isDiagonal=1, isUpper=1, isLower=1]

    InitFlags --> LoopDiag[Loop i=0 to n-1, j=0 to n-1]
    LoopDiag --> CondDiag{i != j AND A i j != 0?}
    CondDiag -- Yes --> SetDiag0[isDiagonal = 0, BREAK]
    CondDiag -- No --> NextDiag[Continue loop]
    NextDiag --> LoopDiag
    SetDiag0 --> DiagCheck{isDiagonal == 1?}

    DiagCheck -- Yes --> ReturnDiag[Return DIAGONAL MATRIX]
    DiagCheck -- No --> LoopUpper[Loop i=0 to n-1, j=0 to i-1]

    LoopUpper --> CondUpper{A i j != 0?}
    CondUpper -- Yes --> SetUpper0[isUpper = 0, BREAK]
    CondUpper -- No --> NextUpper[Continue loop]
    NextUpper --> LoopUpper
    SetUpper0 --> UpperCheck{isUpper == 1?}

    UpperCheck -- Yes --> ReturnUpper[Return UPPER TRIANGULAR MATRIX]
    UpperCheck -- No --> LoopLower[Loop i=0 to n-1, j=i+1 to n-1]

    LoopLower --> CondLower{A i j != 0?}
    CondLower -- Yes --> SetLower0[isLower = 0, BREAK]
    CondLower -- No --> NextLower[Continue loop]
    NextLower --> LoopLower
    SetLower0 --> LowerCheck{isLower == 1?}

    LowerCheck -- Yes --> ReturnLower[Return LOWER TRIANGULAR MATRIX]
    LowerCheck -- No --> ReturnNone[Return NONE OF THE SPECIAL TYPES]

    NotSquare --> End([Send result to client])
    ReturnDiag --> End
    ReturnUpper --> End
    ReturnLower --> End
    ReturnNone --> End

    style Start fill:#90EE90
    style End fill:#FFB6C1
    style ReturnDiag fill:#87CEEB
    style ReturnUpper fill:#FFD700
    style ReturnLower fill:#DDA0DD
    style ReturnNone fill:#FFA07A
    style NotSquare fill:#FF6347
```

