# Section 5: KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

---

## 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question A1 `[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023, Model Exam]`

**Differentiate between TCP and UDP with respect to connection type, reliability, and typical use cases.**

#### Model Answer (3 marks):

| Parameter | TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) | UDP (User Datagram Protocol) |
|-----------|-------------------------------------|------------------------------|
| **Connection Type** | Connection-oriented (requires 3-way handshake) | Connectionless (no handshake) |
| **Reliability** | Reliable — uses ACKs, retransmission, sequence numbers | Unreliable — best-effort delivery, no ACKs |
| **Use Cases** | Web (HTTP/HTTPS), Email (SMTP), SSH, FTP | Video streaming, DNS, VoIP, online gaming |
| **Header Size** | 20 bytes (minimum) | 8 bytes |
| **Speed** | Slower due to overhead | Faster due to minimal overhead |

**Mark Distribution:** 1 mark for table headers + 1 mark for 3 comparison rows + 1 mark for accurate examples.

