### 2.4 Key Structural Memory Hooks

- **`struct sockaddr_in` fields:** `sin_family = AF_INET`, `sin_port = htons(PORT)`, `sin_addr.s_addr = inet_addr("127.0.0.1")` or `INADDR_ANY`.
- **`INADDR_ANY`** = **0.0.0.0** — server accepts connections on *any* of its network interfaces.
- **Port number range:** the well-known port **8080** is a common teaching port (avoids the privileged port issue with port < 1024).
- **Zombie process prevention:** Use `signal(SIGCHLD, SIG_IGN)` or `waitpid(-1, NULL, WNOHANG)` in the parent to reap terminated children. ⚠️ *Exam favourite!*

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Real-world engineering utility:** This exact pattern (a TCP listener that forks per connection) powers **early HTTP servers, FTP daemons, Telnet, SSH (pre-fork model), and SMTP**. Modern variants use **`select()` / `poll()` / `epoll()`** or thread pools (e.g., **Nginx, Apache prefork, HAProxy**) for higher scalability.

