> [!WARNING]
> **🚨 KTU Examiner's Pitfall Callout — Common Mark-Deducting Mistakes:**
> 1. **Forgetting `htons(PORT)`** — port assigned in host byte order. Result: server binds to wrong port. **−1 mark.**
> 2. **Not closing `sockfd` in the child** — file-descriptor leak; under stress, the server will exhaust descriptors and `accept()` will fail. **−2 marks.**
> 3. **Not closing `newsockfd` in the parent** — same FD leak issue; also, on server restart you get *bind: address already in use*. **−1 mark.**
> 4. **Calling `fork()` but treating parent and child identically** — must use `if (pid == 0)` to differentiate. **−2 marks.**
> 5. **Using `read()`/`write()` return value as a string without null-termination** — buffer not null-terminated, undefined behaviour on `printf`. **−1 mark.**
> 6. **Not including `<arpa/inet.h>`** — `htons`, `inet_aton` not declared → compilation error. **−0.5 marks.**
> 7. **Hard-coding client IP without using `argv`** — loses portability marks. **−1 mark.**

